  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\n\n### User Story\n\nAs a user, I want to work with application regardless of the app window size.\n\n### Description\n*Type*: Bug\n\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\n*Summary*:  several issues can be replicated when you resize application window.\n\n**1) Automatic scroll to latest massage after resize**\nIf initially you are somewhere in the middle of chat history, you automatically pulled back to the latest message after resize\nVideo is [here](http://take.ms/6k9xv)\n\n**2) CPU consumption jumps to 70-100% during resize**\nVideo is [here](http://take.ms/vE0hy)\nLog is [here](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2187957/StatusIm.txt)\n\n**3) Chat headers and  messages are displayed in a column in a small-size window and doesn't get back if you resize window to normal size again**\n#### Regular size\n- Chat header\n![regul](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/42625877-82eeb920-85d1-11e8-9de2-7dafca16f13a.png)\n- Messages\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/42626172-4f936c78-85d2-11e8-9a00-ce59f80433fb.png)\n\n#### Small size\n- Chat header\n![png 2018-07-12 12-52-45](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/42626346-bebe043c-85d2-11e8-91dc-228b048aceed.png)\n- Messages\n![am_size](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/42626091-0ef6f806-85d2-11e8-80a2-da1e92c66b35.png)\n\n#### Recized to regular size after small\n- Chat header\n![png 2018-07-12 12-53-26](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/42626336-b5869c58-85d2-11e8-977e-752ae0d61070.png)\n- Messages\n![rel](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/42626009-e3c56a32-85d1-11e8-8630-0ac9fab99cee.png)\n\n**4) There is no fixed smallest side for window** \nFor Slack smallest window size is: 345X932\nFor Telegram: 484X873\nIn all cases user can use most app features.\nFor Status desktop there are no limits, and you can resize window to a state when it is not possible to work with application (screenshot below is resized window)\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/42626832-f905a8c4-85d3-11e8-9e3e-28020b325df6.png)\n\n**5) Tab-bar overlaps with the list of settings in the profile**\n<img width=\"201\" alt=\"dfsdf\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/52709726-d3187380-2f8d-11e9-8e81-c50087bfcc55.png\">\n\n### Solution\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\n*Summary*: \n\n- [ ] Add smallest fixed size, where application can be usable\n- [ ] Reduce CPU consumption during resize\n- [ ] Fix issue with automatic scroll\n- [x] Fix issue with displaying messages/chat header in a row\n- [ ] Fix issue with overlapping tabs and profile\n\n### Additional Information\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\n* Status version: [desktop_build_11.07.2018](https://jenkins.status.im/job/status-react/job/desktop/job/manual/47/)\n* Operating System: Mac OSx High Sierra",
